Russian Equity Movers: Norilsk Nickel, Polymetal, Rosneft Move

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-08-05T16:03:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-05/russian-equity-movers-norilsk-nickel-polymetal-rosneft-move.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  slipped 2.1
percent to 1,587.77 by the 6:45 p.m. close in Moscow. The
dollar-denominated RTS Index slumped 3.1 percent to 1,798.75.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO GMK Norilsk Nickel (GMKN RX),  Russia ’s biggest mining
company, dropped for a fourth day, falling 1 percent to 7,066
rubles as metals declined on concern that the global economy is
slowing.  OAO Polymetal (PMTL RX), a Russian silver producer,
retreated 1.9 percent to 523.9 rubles as the metal dropped in
 London .  OAO Rosneft (ROSN RX), Russia’s largest oil producer, fell
2.5 percent to 219.37 rubles after oil plunged in  New York  on
speculation fuel demand will falter as the global economic
recovery stalls.  To contact the reporter on this story:
